==English==
{{wikipedia}}

===Etymology===
French, from Middle French, from [[present participle]] of [[bouffer]] to [[puff]]

===Pronunciation===
{{rfp}}
bü-'fänt

===Adjective===
'''bouffant'''
# Of hair or clothing, full-bodied or [[puffy]]; [[puffed]] out away from head or body.
#: ''Her '''bouffant''' suit made her seem much heavier than her petite figure actually was.''

===Noun===
'''bouffant'''
# A popular [[hairstyle]] in the mid-to-late 16th century, nowadays common with [[poodle]]s.

